{"lemma":"دِفْلَى","slug":"دِفْلَى","root":"د.ف.ل","root_slug":"د-ف-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/د-ف-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n12755"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D9%90%D9%81%D9%92%D9%84%D9%8E%D9%89"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"oleander (Nerium oleander)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Ancient Greek δάφνη (dáphnē)."},"ipa":["/dif.laː/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n12755","headword_ar":"دِفْلَى","root":"dfl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, K, &c.,) accord. to those who make the alif to be a sign of the fem. gender; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"difolFY","text_ar":"دِفْلًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to those who make that letter to be one of quasi-coordination; used alike as a sing. and a pl.; (S;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"difolN","text_ar":"دِفْلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Ibn-'Abbád, K;) [the first of these appellations applied in the present day to The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rose-bay,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"laurel-bay; oleander, nerium oleander, rhododendron,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rhododaphne:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"common laurel:"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain tree,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bitter,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very bitter,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and poisonous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"green, and beautiful in appearance, the blossom of which is beautifully tinged,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"called in Persian"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xarozahoraho","text_ar":"خَرْزَهْرَهْ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"there is a river-kind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a land-kind: the leaves are like those of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamoqaA='","text_ar":"حَمْقَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gardenpurslane"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"but more slender; and the branches,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"twigs, are long, spreading over the ground; at the leaves are thorns; and it grows in waste places: the river-kind grows upon the banks of rivers; its thorns are unconspicuous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unapparent; its leaves are like those of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xilaAf","text_ar":"خِلَاف"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"salix Aegyptia"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and of the almond, broad; and the upper part of its stem is thicker than the lower part thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is very deadly: its blossom is like the red rose,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very rough"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"x$n jd~A","text_ar":"خشن جدّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[but this I think is a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasanN jid~FA","text_ar":"حَسَنٌ جِدًّا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very beautiful"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and upon it is a kind of tuft like hair:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its fruit is like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuronuwb","text_ar":"خُرْنُوب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having an aperient,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a deobstruent, property; and stuffed with a substance like wool:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is good for the mange,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scab, and the itch"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hik~ap","text_ar":"حِكَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"used in the manner of a liniment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and especially the expressed juice of its leaves;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and for pain of the knee and the back,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of long duration,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"applied in the manner of a poultice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plaster; and for expelling fleas and the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"insect called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araD","text_ar":"اَرَض"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by the sprinkling of a decoction thereof; and the rubbing over with the heart thereof twelve times, after cleansing, is good for removing the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"malignant leprosy termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraS","text_ar":"بَرَص"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and its leaves put upon hard tumours are very beneficial: but it is a poison:"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yet"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sometimes it is mixed with wine and rue, and given to be drunk, and saves from the poisons of venomous reptiles:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the Ra-ees [Ibn-Seenà, or Avicenna,] says that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is perilous by itself, and its blossom, to men, and to horses and the like, and to dogs, but is beneficial when made into a decoction with rue, and drunk:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) IAar says that the ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trees termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A='","text_ar":"ا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alaA='","text_ar":"اَلَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hbr","text_ar":"حبر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabor","text_ar":"خَبْر"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a species of lote-tree,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] are all called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"difolaY","text_ar":"دِفْلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T.) AHn says that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zanod","text_ar":"زَنْد"},{"kind":"text","text":"made from the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"difolaY","text_ar":"دِفْلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is excellent for producing fire: and hence the prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiqodaHo bidifolaY fiY maroxi vum~a $ud~a baEodu A^awo A^aroxi","text_ar":"اِقْدَحْ بِدِفْلَى فِى مَرْخِ ثُمَّ شُدَّ بَعْدُ اَوْ اَرْخِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Endeavour thou to produce fire with wood of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dflY","text_ar":"دفلى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon wood of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mrx","text_ar":"مرخ"},{"kind":"text","text":":"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"then tighten afterwards or loosen"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (M:) said when one incites a bad man against another bad man: (M, Meyd:) or, accord. to IAar, said in relation to a man whom one needs not to press, or importune. (Meyd.)"}],"source_refs":["T","M","S","K","TA","Meyd"]}]}}